What are arrays used for?
arrays are used to store multiple entries of the same type of data

What is the code for an int array?
int[] asdf = new int[];

What is the code for an String array?
String[] asdf = new String[];

What is the code for an boolean array?
boolean[] asdf = new boolean[];

What is the code for an double array?
double[] asdf = new double[];

How would you change the first value of the int array to 42?
intarray[1] = 42;

Of the String array to "Bob"?
stringarray[1] = "Bob"

What does this do: private String[] dessert = new String[3];
creates a stringg array named dessert with 3 slots for data

What does this do: private String[] postres = {"rice pudding", "pan dulce", "bunuelos"}
makes a string array with the values rice updding, pan dulce, and bunuelos held within it

How are they different?
one creates an aray with 3 null values, one creates an array with 3 spots that have strings in them

How would we replace "bunuelos" with "apple pie"?
postres[3] = "apple pie";
